<setup>

  <selectFromSequence name="a" from="1.4" to="1.8" step="0.1" />
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from="0" to="2" step="0.5" />  
  <selectFromSequence name="c" from="-0.54" to="0.56" step="0.1" /> 

  <math name="ABSb"><abs>$b</abs></math>
  
  <function name="g" symbolic="false">-1*$a^x + $b</function>
  <derivative name="gP" symbolic="false">$g</derivative>  
  <derivative name="gPP" symbolic="false">$gP</derivative>    
  <function name="L" symbolic="false" styleNumber="2" labelPosition="lowerRight">$$gP($c)(x-$c) + $$g($c)</function>  
    <point name="A" styleNumber="6" coords="($c,$$g($c))" showCoordsWhenDragging="false" draggable="false" labelPosition="upperRight"> 
      <label><m>A = $A.coords</m></label>
    </point> 
    <point name="B" styleNumber="6" coords="($c+0.6*$a,$$L($c+0.6*$a))" showCoordsWhenDragging="false" draggable="false" labelPosition="upperRight"> 
      <label><m>B = $B.coords</m></label>
    </point>

  <label name="gLabel" anchor="(-3,$$g(-3)-0.25)"><m>y = g(x)</m></label>
  <label name="LLabel" anchor="(-2.5,$$L(-2.5)+0.5)"><m>y = L(x)</m></label>
  
</setup>

  <p>Let <m>g</m> be the function given by the graph below and <m>L</m> its tangent line approximation at the point <m>A</m>.</p>

<!--  <p><m>a = $a</m>, <m>b = $b</m>, and <m>c = $c</m>, so <m>g(x) = $$g(x)</m> and <m>L(x) = $$L(x)</m>, plus <m>A = $A</m> and <m>B = $B</m></p> -->

      <graph xmin="-4" xmax="4" ymin="-4" ymax="4" size="medium" grid="false" showNavigation="false" displayXAxis="false" displayYAxis="false"> $g $L $A $B $gLabel $LLabel
      </graph>


<p>

  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        State the formula for <m>L(x)</m>, the tangent line approximation to <m>g</m> at the point <m>($c,$$g($c))</m>.  Be sure to use all of the available accuracy in the given data.
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>L(x)=</m><answer><award allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute> $$g($c) + $$gP($c)(x-$c)
        </award></answer>.
      </p>  
    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        Use the tangent line approximation to estimate the value of <m>g(<math simplify>$c+0.25*$a</math>)</m>.   Be sure to use all of the available accuracy in the given data.
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>g(<math simplify>$c+0.25*$a</math>) \approx</m><answer><award allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute> $$g($c) + $$gP($c)(0.25*$a)
        </award></answer>.
      </p> 
    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        The estimated value of  <m>g(<math simplify>$c+0.25*$a</math>)</m> found in (b) is 
        <answer>
          <choiceInput name="overunder" inline>
            <choice>greater than</choice>
            <choice>less than</choice>
            <choice>equal to</choice>
          </choiceInput>            
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=1 and $$gPP($c) < 0    
              </when>
            </award>  
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=2 and $$gPP($c) > 0 
              </when> 
            </award>
          </answer> the true value of <m>g(<math simplify>$c+0.25*$a</math>)</m>. One reason this conclusion is true is the tangent line lies 
               <answer>
                      <choiceInput name="reason" inline>
                        <choice>below</choice>
                        <choice>above</choice>
                      </choiceInput>            
                        <award>
                          <when>$reason.selectedIndices=2 and $$gPP($c) < 0    
                          </when>
                        </award>  
                        <award>
                          <when>$reason.selectedIndices=1 and $$gPP($c) > 0 
                          </when> 
                        </award>
                </answer>  
                the curve.
              </p> 
    </li>  
  </ol>  
  
</p>  


   